Class IterativeRootApproximation<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.myorb.math.computational.IterativeProcessingSupport<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - data type for calculations
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IterativeRootApproximationOverDomain

    public class IterativeRootApproximation<T>
extends IterativeProcessingSupportTabular<T>
    calculate function root with iterative adjustment specified by Newton's method. first order Newton-Raphson takes just 1st derivative, Newton 2nd order requires 2nd derivative.
    Author:
    Michael Druckman
